The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 City giants Mohammedan Sporting suspended Mike Okoro and lodged a complaint in the AIFF for the Nigerians indiscipline on Thursday. The clubs general secretary Sultan Ahmed said he (Okoro) left four months ago, and did not turn up for the NFL even after taking more than half of his contractual amount. However, there was some good news for Mohammedan Sporting, who are slated to face Mahindra United at Salt Lake Stadium on Saturday. Malaysian Preston Caparol and Nigerian Endem signed for the club, while their former player Eric Mputu who had left for his native place joined the club ahead of their Round V NFL tie.

 CRPF and BSF were adjudged joint winners in the team championship of the West Bengal State Judo Championship held on Saturday. 

 RESULTS

 The Howrah District Boxing Association (HDBA) with 17 points emerged as the team champions in the 39th West Bengal State Junior Boxing Championship (Boys), while Kidderpore SOPC (11 points) had to be content with the runners-up position. Nazir Khan of Durgapur Steel Plant was adjudged Best Boxer.

 CRICKET: CAB Inter-School Tournament (Under-19) Final St. James School vs National High School at Eden Gardens from 9 am. 

 GENERAL: Inter-City Sports Carnival at various venues.




